This is a collection of scripts to automate things by using
CircuitPython to pretend to be a keyboard or mouse.

You need:

 1. A script (found here)
 2. A CircuitPython board.  Can be as cheap as $10: https://www.adafruit.com/product/3500
 3. An adapter to connect to your device.  The official Apple ones are here: https://www.apple.com/shop/product/MK0W2AM/A/lightning-to-usb-3-camera-adapter . There are many knockoffs on Amazon for $10-$20
 4. A cable to connect the board to the adapter.  Usually any old MicroUSB cable will do.

== Setting up your device ==

 1. Update to the latest CircuitPython for your board
 2. Get the adafruit_hid library from here: https://github.com/adafruit/Adafruit_CircuitPython_Bundle .
 3. Unzip the bundle and copy lib/adafruit_hid to your device: CIRCUITPY/lib
 4. Copy a script to the device, like: "cat foo.py > /media/user/CIRCUITPY/code.py"
 5. Plug the abom
